help.fullHelp.header:
{{emoji}} **Hello! I'm Ayana!**

Below you can see all the commands I know.
If you need further help with something join our [Support Server]({{invite}}).

**Have a nice day!**
help.fullHelp.info:
**Use `{{catHelp}}` for more information about a category.
Use `{{cmdHelp}}` for more information about a command.**

**Examples:**
`{{prefix}}help ayana` for an overview of the AYANA category.
`{{prefix}}help music` for detailed help for the music command.
help.aliases.desc.list: Lists all aliases created in this server
help.aliases.desc.userargs: Allows or denies arguments, options and flags to be added to the alias when it's executed
help.aliases.desc.createAlias:
Type the command as you would normally do and add '--addalias <alias>' to the end of it.
    Let's say you want to make '{{prefix}}hello' as an alias for '{{prefix}}say hello'.
    To add this alias you would execute '{{prefix}}say hello --addalias hello'.
    Options and flags are also saved when an alias is added (except --addalias of course).

help.music.desc.queue: Shows Queue or Enqueues a song/playlist
help.music.desc.enqueueNext: Enqueues a song/playlist as next item

help.perms.desc.allow: Allows a permission node (append exactly one of the options listed below)
help.perms.desc.default: Defaults a permission node (append exactly one of the options listed below)
help.perms.desc.deny: Denies a permission node (append exactly one of the options listed below)
help.perms.desc.show: Shows permissions (append exactly one of the options listed below)
help.perms.desc.channelUser: Sets or shows channel user permissions
help.perms.desc.channelRole: Sets or shows channel role permissions
help.perms.desc.note:
The permissions are in the order of the options, that means that channel user
    is the highest level and server (guild) is the lowest level.
help.pick.short: Let me help you when you can't decide
help.prune.desc.pruneUntil: Prunes messages until the given message is reached
help.prune.desc.bots: Prunes all messages created by any bot
help.prune.desc.user: Prunes all messages by the specified user
help.prune.desc.filter: Only prunes messages that contain the specified string
help.prune.desc.attachments: Only prunes messages containing attachments (can be combined with --embeds)
help.prune.desc.embeds: Only prunes messages containing embeds (can be combined with --attachments)
help.prune.desc.pinned: Also prunes pinned messages (they are not pruned by default)

help.prune.desc.reactions: Only removes the reactions from the targeted messages instead of deleting them
help.prune.desc.silent: Silent. Disables print of the prune results at the end
help.reminder.desc.remove: Removes a reminder by search or ID
help.reminder.desc.list: Shows a list of your reminders

help.role.desc.bots: Will only change roles for bots
help.role.desc.users: Will only change roles for users
help.role.desc.user: Will only change roles for specified users
help.role.desc.inrole: Will only change roles if the target has the specified role
help.role.desc.notinrole: Will only change roles if the target doesn't have the specified role
help.role.desc.noroles: Will only change roles if the target doesn't have any roles
help.role.desc.name: Renames a role
help.role.desc.color: Changes the color of a role
help.role.desc.moveAfter: Sets role position after target role
help.role.desc.note:
This command will not allow you to give, take or modify roles
